            "title": "Short- and long-term corneal vascular effects of tafluprost eye drops.",
            "abstract": "Prostaglandin analogs are first line therapy in the treatment of glaucoma, but also display side effects during ocular inflammation. In this context, the potential side effects of prostaglandin analogs on the normally avascular cornea, the main application route for eye drops, are so far not fully defined. Therefore, the aim of this study was to evaluate the vascular effects of the prostaglandin analog tafluprost on the healthy and inflamed cornea.",
